        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 4:42PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 442 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles north of Greenhorn Mountain, or 24 miles southwest of Pueblo,
moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Beulah and Oak Ridge Burn Scar.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
